Under the "Jal Jeevan Mission Programme," Md. Nimbara Ta. Barsheeti tap water supply scheme has been awarded the Goods and Services Tax (GST) rate plus additional rate of tender as well as technicalities.
Government Decision No: Suprama-2025 / P.No.216 / Papu RAE Office No-1368445)
Due to these changes, the price of the scheme has increased by Rs. The revised price of 27.69 lakh (Rupees thirty-nine lakh and seventy-nine thousand only) is being approved by the Administrator.
Conditions
1) The CEO / Chief Engineer will be responsible for completing all the remaining works within the prescribed time frame at the above mentioned revised cost.
2) The original administrative approval agreed upon for the scheme as well as the terms and conditions mentioned while granting the revised technical approval should be strictly adhered to.

3) On completion of the scheme, it should be handed over to the concerned Gram Panchayat. The concerned Gram Panchayat / Zilla Parishad shall be responsible for taking over the scheme within one month from the date of receipt of intimation from the concerned Executive Engineer, Rural Water Supply Department, Zila Parishad that the scheme has been actually completed. Immediately after the actual completion of the scheme, a joint inspection of the scheme should be conducted by the concerned Executive Engineer, Zilla Parishad and concerned Gram Panchayat officials and any defects found in such inspection should be corrected before handing over the scheme.

4) The Gram Panchayat / Zilla Parishad concerned shall not receive any assistance from the Government for the implementation of the scheme, maintenance, repairs (subject to special modifications), depreciation in the scheme or renovation of machinery to meet the recurring expenditure incurred every year.
5) On completion of the scheme, it will be mandatory for the local body (concerned Gram Panchayat / Zila Parishad) to implement the scheme. The accounts of the scheme should also be closed.

6) A CAG report in 2013 shows that 21 per cent of water supply schemes in the state have been shut down due to poor maintenance / non-payment of electricity bills. In order for ARTA to be more efficient, the responsibility of increasing the water table rate as per requirement will be with the respective Gram Panchayats / Zila Parishads.
7) Action should be taken in accordance with the prevailing policy on extortion.
8) It shall be the responsibility of the Zilla Parishad that the present scheme shall not be revised under any circumstances.
9) Since no administrative expenditure is admissible under the Jal Jeevan Mission, it should be excluded if 4% of the administrative expenditure has been taken up in the revised budget of the scheme.
10) It should be ensured at the Zilla Parishad level that the tendering process of the scheme is carried out properly.
